  <!-- Venue -->
  <section class="sd-section">
    <div class="sd-section-head"><h2>About the venue</h2></div>
    <div class="sd-prose">
      <p>The Junipero Serra Museum sits on a hilltop in Presidio Park, overlooking Mission Valley and the San Diego River. Built in 1929 in Spanish Colonial Revival style, it marks the site where Father Junipero Serra established the first Spanish mission in California in 1769.</p>
      <p>Panoramic views, white stucco architecture, gardens. The hilltop setting means golden-hour photos will be excellent.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

